data.title: Weather in Llano County 2020
data.meta_description: What is the weather like in Llano County? Average temperatures, precipitation and wind.
data.text:
Llano County weather Q&A

What is the warmest month in Llano County?

The warmest month is August with an average temperature of 99 °F over the past years.

What is the coldest month in Llano County?

The coldest month is January with an average daytime temperature of 61 °F in the past few years.

Which month is the wettest in Llano County?

Chance of precipitation is the highest in November with a probability of around 4.2 %.
